cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the optimization of data dissemination in IoT networks, which involves communication protocols, network infrastructure, and performance metrics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses stochastic geometry to analyze the performance of the network, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with optimizing conflicting performance objectives, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper uses a comprehensive performance metric, which falls under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing the carrier sensing threshold, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
